<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="809" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/139.</note>
                        <head>[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-22"><hi rend="italic">November 22,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The embassy has received a note from the foreign office which states that
                            President Diaz has no authority to permit the erection of levees or to
                            grant free entry of materials for the work. The negotiation of a treaty
                            is suggested and the Mexican ambassador at Washington has received
                            detailed and specific instructions as to terms. Congressional action
                            must be taken concerning the free entry of materials.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>